    <%= image_tag("content/truck_rear_underride_guard_cropped.jpg", alt: "Photo of the rear of a truck from the side, showing the metal bars that form the underride guard at the back of the truck.") %>

    <p>Imagine the back of a semi-truck trailer.</p>

    <p>It's hard to imagine that a car could fit under there. There are bars, called underride guards, at the back of the truck to stop cars from riding under the truck.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>The underride guards don't always stop cars from going under the truck.</li>
      <li>Even at low speeds cars can end up under there!</li>
      <li><strong>Death</strong> of family members is a common result to such crashes.</li>
    </ul>
    <blockquote>
      <p><strong>“It is safer to run into a brick wall then the back of a truck.”</strong></p>
      <cite>Russ Rader, Insurance Institute for Highway Safety<br>May 5, 2014</cite>
    </blockquote>
  </section>
</article>
