  <h1 class="noselect">Hasn't there already been research done on underride guards?</h1>
  <section>
    <p>Although there has already been a lot of research done on underride prevention, there has not been readily available crash testing information to prove its viability or convince government regulators and the trucking industry to move forward with these measures to prevent unnecessary deaths and horrific injuries.</p>
<p>Furthermore, we want to show that this can be done in an affordable manner and that it is a priority to this nation to pay for the best possible protection for pedestrians, cyclists, and motorists on the road.</p>
<p>We hope that the money we raise can provide unquestionable proof that more can be done than currently is and that rear guards, side guards, and front protection on all trucks will become standard. When we found out after losing AnnaLeah and Mary that better protection was possible, our relentless question has been, “If it can be done, why is it not being done?”<p>
<p>For detailed information about underride guards, <a href="http://annaleahmary.com/underride-guards/">there are many articles on annaleahmary.com</a></p>
  </section>
