<article class="retractable start-hidden">
  <h1 class="noselect">Will my donation be tax deductible?</h1>
  <section>
    <p>AnnaLeah &amp; Mary for Truck Safety is incorporated in North Carolina as a non-profit corporation, as of June 26, 2015. We have applied for tax-exempt status (Form 1023) with the IRS (September 4, 2015). This had to be done within 27 months of organizing.</p>
<p>Meanwhile, we have been told by the IRS that we can operate as a 501(c)(3) organization. We meet all of the requirements and have been told that we can communicate that we are eligible to receive contributions that may be tax deductible for the donor. That is the wording which we are told to use and will be the same wording which we would need to use when we actually get an approval letter from IRS. We cannot guarantee that your particular donation will be deductible because that depends on your tax return details.</p>
<p>However, if you donate to AnnaLeah &amp; Mary for Truck Safety, then we will email you a receipt which you can use when you do your taxes. We have organized AL&amp;MFTS to meet the requirements of a 501(c)(3) organization and plan to use all funds received accordingly.</p>
  </section>
